  "prompt": "Which is a good inpatient drug and alcohol rehab center near Washington County AR?",
  "response": "Finding a good inpatient drug and alcohol rehab center near Washington County, AR, involves considering factors like treatment approaches, accreditation, facilities, and reviews. Here are a few reputable options in or near the area:\n\n### 1. **Ozark Guidance (Northwest Arkansas)**\n   - **Location:** Fayetteville, AR (close to Washington County)\n   - **Details:** Ozark Guidance offers comprehensive mental health and substance abuse treatment services, including inpatient and outpatient programs. They provide an integrated approach to care.\n   - **Website:** [www.ozarkguidance.org](http://www.ozarkguidance.org)\n\n### 2. **Decision Point**\n   - **Location:** Bentonville, AR (near Washington County)\n   - **Details:** Decision Point provides inpatient and outpatient treatment for substance use disorders. They focus on holistic recovery, including counseling, therapy, and support groups.\n   - **Website:** [www.decisionpointarkansas.org](https://www.decisionpointarkansas.org)\n\n### 3. **Williamsburg Treatment Center**\n   - **Location:** Fayetteville, AR\n   - **Details:** This facility offers inpatient stays for detoxification and intensive addiction treatment. They provide medically supervised detox and individualized treatment plans.\n   - **Website:** [www.williamsburgtreatmentcenters.com](https://www.williamsburgtreatmentcenters.com)\n\n### 4. **Valley Behavioral Health System**\n   - **Location:** Fort Smith, AR (about 1 hour from Washington County)\n   - **Details:** Valley Behavioral Health offers inpatient and outpatient programs for substance abuse and co-occurring mental health disorders. They have a strong focus on personalized care.\n   - **Website:** [www.valleybehavioral.com](https://www.valleybehavioral.com)\n\n### 5. **New Beginnings Arkansas**\n   - **Location:** Fayetteville, AR\n   - **Details:** This faith-based rehab center offers inpatient and outpatient programs for addiction recovery. They incorporate spiritual guidance and evidence-based therapies.\n   - **Website:** [www.newbeginningsar.com](http://www.newbeginningsar.com)\n\n### Tips for Choosing a Rehab Center:\n- **Accreditation:** Ensure the facility is accredited by organizations like the Joint Commission or CARF.\n- **Insurance:** Verify whether the center accepts your insurance or offers payment plans.\n- **Reviews:** Read reviews or testimonials from former clients.\n- **Services:** Look for facilities that offer tailored treatment plans, including therapy, counseling, and aftercare.\n\nIf you\u2019re unsure which facility is the best fit, consider reaching out to an addiction specialist or a local healthcare provider for guidance.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
